transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Okay, so if I can speak and you can't speak over me and I will be brief, then I can help.

Speaker 2: You.

Speaker 1: What's there to do?

Speaker 2: Can't you just cancel?

Speaker 1: What do I need to do?

Speaker 2: I don't understand.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: So the reason you received the refill is because when you placed the order, the screen popped up, right?

Speaker 1: The terms of service.

Speaker 2: The terms of service.

Speaker 1: The terms of service at the end said, every order with us comes with regular refills mandated by the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: If you want to change those or you don't want those or you want to push those back or whatever,

Speaker 1: this is the phone number to call.

Speaker 2: It gave you the direct phone number to this number, which is me, who you are speaking with right here, right now.

Speaker 1: You did not call that number, so that is why you received that initial refill.

Speaker 2: And assuming that you did place an order for Viagra would assume that you did need a prescription.

Speaker 1: Prescriptions take a lot of care to place an order for.

Speaker 2: Why?

Speaker 1: They go through a pharmacy that is extensive medical information that you would have had to provide to us.

Speaker 2: That means that when you placed the order, we paid for the doctor's fee for the doctor to see you for the prescription.

Speaker 1: Now that is all fine and well, because if you placed the order, that means you needed the prescription.

Speaker 2: Now, if you don't need regular refills, that is totally fine, but if you place an order for a prescription, that usually means you will inevitably at some point need that prescription.

Speaker 1: And that you understand that I'm communicating to you that if you have determined that you no longer need the prescription, that is fine, but we only pay that doctor's fee one time.

Speaker 2: For that reason, because we offer the opportunity to place the prescription on hold.

Speaker 1: Okay, and that is fine.

Speaker 2: I don't want it on hold.

Speaker 1: I want it canceled.

Speaker 2: Okay, great.

Speaker 1: You know where to find us in the future.

Speaker 2: We are at this phone number.

Speaker 1: And yeah, there will just be a note in your file that if you do order again, you do understand all of the terms that I have communicated to you.

Speaker 2: Totally fine.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: That wasn't so complicated, now was it?

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you for speaking over me.

Speaker 1: Yes, we got a lot done together.

Speaker 2: I appreciate you, Jonathan, and I hope you have a great day.
